** We are on the hunt for a CNC operators to join our clients growing team! **   
  
** Who will you be working with? **   
  
Our Client is a locally owned and operated business that specialises in
servicing the industrial sector. With a rich history dating back to 2005, they
have grown to become one of Australia's leading engineering design and
manufacturing companies. Located in Brisbane, their workshop caters to a
diverse range of small, medium, and large industrial manufacturers across
various sectors. Their commitment is to provide high-quality machine
automation products, systems, and solutions, and ensure clients receive full
support from the concept stage through to production.  
  
As a CNC Operator, you will be an integral part of a dedicated team of
professionals. Your role will involve the manufacturing of mechanical
components and machinery, contributing to the success of projects in the
industrial sector. If you have a strong background in CNC operations and are
looking for an exciting opportunity to work with a reputable company, we
encourage you to apply.  
  
** What are the benefits? **

  * Join a well-established and growing company with a strong reputation in the industry. 
  * Collaborate with a dedicated and enthusiastic team of professionals. 
  * Opportunity for career development and growth within the organization. 
  * Competitive compensation and benefits package. 
  * Work on exciting industrial projects and contribute to the success of the company 
** What will you be doing? **

  * Operating & maintenance of CNC machinery. 
  * Read and interpret technical drawings and blueprints. 
  * Conduct routine maintenance and inspections to ensure machinery operates smoothly. 
  * Collaborate with project managers, engineers, and other team members to meet project goals. 
  * Maintain accurate records of maintenance and repair work. 
** What do you need? **

  * Qualification as a CNC operator or relevant certification, 
  * Proven experience as a CNC Operator, preferably in an industrial or manufacturing environment. 
  * Proficiency in reading and interpreting technical drawings and blueprints. 
  * Strong mechanical aptitude and problem-solving skills. 
  * Familiarity with various hand and power tools used in fitting and machining. 
  * Commitment to safety and quality in all aspects of work. 
